      "end": 19.2,
      "text": "Read by Cara Schalenberg, www.kray.org.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-004",
      "start": 19.64,
      "end": 20.82,
      "text": "ASIP's Fables.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-005",
      "start": 22.8,
      "end": 24.86,
      "text": "The Dog in the Manger.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-006",
      "start": 27.34,
      "end": 32.34,
      "text": "A dog was lying in a manger on the hay, which had been put there for the cattle.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-007",
      "start": 32.86,
      "end": 36.6,
      "text": "And when they came and tried to eat, he growled and snapped at them,",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-008",
      "start": 36.94,
      "end": 38.7,
      "text": "and wouldn't let them get at their food.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-009",
      "start": 39.82,
      "end": 43.46,
      "text": "What a selfish beast! said one of them to his companions.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-010",
      "start": 44.52,
      "end": 48.7,
      "text": "He can't eat himself, and yet he won't let those eat who can.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-011",
      "start": 50.62,
      "end": 52.86,
      "text": "End of the Dog in the Manger.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-012",
      "start": 53.98,
      "end": 59.24,
      "text": "Recorded on February 4th, 2006, in Oceanside, California.",
      "note": ""
    }
  ],
